AGI - The investigation of a sale of votes in Triggiano, in the Barese, blows the table of the centerleft on the rules of the primaries > which should have designated the candidate in the Apulian capital. The investigations also covered an Apulian regional junta councillor led by the dem, Michele Emiliano, who resigned today. He was also arrested by the Councillor's husband. For this reason Giuseppe Conte>, coming to Bari, has made it known that for the Movement 5 Stars there are no longer conditions for primaries of coalition >.
And, therefore, the pentastellati will support Michele Laforgia, the name on which Sinistra Italiana also points. On the other hand, with Vito Leccese, remain the Democratic Party and the other half of Avs, the green one of Angelo Bonelli. A move, that of Conte, which cuts half the front of the centerleft, always that one of the parties in question does not give up to its candidate. But judging by the irritation that filters from Nazareno, this does not seem to be the scenario that prepares. "The choice of Conte to leave the primary is incomprehensible, if the M5s thinks of winning alone against the right, proceed as well," they emphasize from the headquarters dem demming any possible hypothesis to converge on Laforgia>.
<div </div
&nbsp;
"Have respect for the city of Bari, for the voters of the centre-left and do not think of giving lectures of morality to anyone", add the dems underlined that "the Pd remains alongside Bari that has already demonstrated how important the Pd is as the presidio of legality and good administration. We are sure that the PD will win the elections against this right again." "Gravissima" the choice of Conte also for Debora Serracchiani, > Head of Justice of the PD, for which "the city of Bari and the Baris do not deserve it.&nbsp; and even the Pd that in decades of hard work has demonstrated in the fact of being on the side of legality and politics that does not bend to the mistrust and mafias. Conte does not think of giving us legal licenses," adds Serracchiani.
"Our party and above all our secretary who represents it does not have to hide a past or political choices that are not relevant to ethics and morality, has a biography mirrored in the struggle for legality. To question him for his own electoral accounts is miserable," says Marco Furfaro, > of the secretariat dem.
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
Before Count left the primary table, the secretary of the Pd, Elly Schlein, warned: "The affair of Triggiano if the charges will be confirmed is very serious." The Democratic Party line is very clear: we do not accept dirty votes," Schlein said. "We don't tolerate votes. We took the effort to change the Pd and we are working on low head every day to build an alternative to this right. On this line and on legality we will not return a millimeter." &nbsp;
